Anti-corruption detectives on Wednesday raided and searched the homes of Samburu Governor Moses Kasaine in Samburu and the capital Nairobi. Sources at the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission (EACC) told the Nation that the investigators were looking for files related to fishy expenditure of Sh2 billion. Also raided were residences and offices of county chief officers implicated in the alleged scandal. "We are targeting the governor, chief officers, directors and contractors for wanton misappropriation of public funds amounting to Sh2 billion," the source told the Nation.  More follows.  